Privacy Policy
Thank you for choosing Blood Pressure - Health Monitor ("the App"). This
            Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our App. By
            downloading and using the App, you consent to the practices described in this policy.
Information We Collect
1. Blood Pressure Data:
When you use the App, you may voluntarily enter and store your blood pressure measurements. This
            data is stored locally on your device and is not transmitted to our servers.
2. Health Data:
You
            may choose to input additional health-related information, such as heart rate or medication schedules. This
            data is also stored locally on your device.
3. Device Information:
We may collect device-specific information, including your device type, operating system, and
            unique device identifiers. This information helps us troubleshoot technical issues and improve the App's
            performance.
Use of Information
We use the information collected for the following purposes:
1. Health Monitoring:
To enable you to track and monitor your blood pressure and overall health.
2. App Improvement:
To enhance and optimize the performance of the App.
3. Technical Support:
To provide customer support and address any technical issues.
Data Security
We take data security seriously. Your health information is stored
            locally on your device, and we do not have access to it. We implement reasonable security measures to
            protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure.
Sharing of Information
We do not share your personal health information with third parties. Your
            data is stored solely on your device.
Children's Privacy
Blood Pressure - Health Monitor is not intended for individuals under the
            age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn that we have
            inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 13, we will promptly delete it.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or
            legal requirements. We encourage you to periodically review this page for updates. Your continued use of the
            App after the revised Privacy Policy's effective date signifies your acceptance of the changes.
Contact Us
If you have any inquiries or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our
            privacy practices, please contact us at bloodpressurei2@outlook.com. We will make every effort to respond to
            your inquiries promptly.
By using Blood Pressure - Health Monitor, you acknowledge that you have
            read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the
collection, use, and disclosure of your information as outlined herein.